      • visitFile

        public boolean visitFile(VirtualFile file)
        Simple visiting method. On returning true a visitor will proceed to file's children, on false - to file's next sibling.
        Parameters:
        file - a file to visit.
        Returns:
        true to proceed to file's children, false to skip to file's next sibling.

      • visitFileEx

        public VirtualFileVisitor.Result visitFileEx(VirtualFile file)
        Extended visiting method.
        Parameters:
        file - a file to visit.
        Returns:
        CONTINUE to proceed to file's children,
        SKIP_CHILDREN to skip to file's next sibling,
        result of skipTo(VirtualFile) to skip to given file's next sibling.

      • afterChildrenVisited

        public void afterChildrenVisited(VirtualFile file)
        This method is only called if visiting wasn't interrupted (by returning skip-requesting result from visitFile(VirtualFile) or visitFileEx(VirtualFile) methods).
        Parameters:
        file - a file whose children were successfully visited.

      • getChildrenIterable

        public java.lang.Iterable<VirtualFile> getChildrenIterable(VirtualFile file)
        By default, visitor uses (VirtualFile.getChildren()) to iterate over file's children. You can override this method to implement another mechanism.
        Parameters:
        file - a virtual file to get children from.
        Returns:
        children iterable, or null to use VirtualFile.getChildren().

      • setValueForChildren

        public final void setValueForChildren(T value)
        Stores the value to this visitor. The stored value can be retrieved later by calling the getCurrentValue(). The visitor maintains the stack of stored values. I.e: This value is held here only during the visiting the current file and all its children. As soon as the visitor finished with the current file and all its subtree and returns to the level up, the value is cleared and the getCurrentValue() returns the previous value, which was stored here before this method call.
